        <h2 class="post-title">How to Remove Acne</h2>
        <div class="post">
            <h3>1.Topical Treatments</h3>
             Over-the-counter creams or gels containing ingredients like benzoyl peroxide, salicylic acid, or
             retinoids can effectively target acne and reduce inflammation.
            <h3>2.Prescription Medications</h3>
             In more severe cases, a dermatologist may prescribe topical or oral antibiotics, hormonal treatments, or
             isotretinoin, a potent acne-fighting medication.
            <h3>3.Professional Treatments</h3>
             Dermatological procedures, such as chemical peels, microdermabrasion, or laser therapy, can be effective in treating stubborn acne.
        </div>

        <h2 class="post-title">How to Prevent Acne</h2>
        <div class="post">
            <h3>1.Maintain a Consistent Skincare Routine</h3>
             Cleanse your face twice daily with a mild cleanser and avoid harsh scrubs.
             Moisturize with a non-comedogenic product suitable for your skin type.

            <h3>2.Hands Off</h3>
             Avoid touching your face frequently, as it can transfer bacteria and exacerbate acne.

            <h3>3.Balanced Diet</h3>
             Consume a diet rich in fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean proteins while reducing high-sugar and high-dairy items.

            <h3>4.Manage Stress</h3>
             Engage in relaxation techniques like yoga, meditation, or exercise to help reduce stress levels and minimize hormonal fluctuations.
